  "chunk_provenance": {
    "The Government of Armenia approved the Nationally Determined Contributions (2021-2030) with an unconditional target to reduce emissions by 40% below 1990 levels by 2030.": 0,
    "Under the Republic of Armenia Energy Sector Development Strategic Program (till 2040), Armenia plans to increase solar generation to at least 15% of total electricity generation (or 1.8 billion kWh) by 2030.": 0,
    "Armenia plans to construct about 1000 MW of solar power plants (including autonomous ones) by 2030 to support reaching solar generation targets.": 0,
    "Armenia plans to commission the Masrik-1 utility-scale solar PV plant (55 MW peak) by 2022 and hold tenders for additional solar PV plants totaling about 520 MW (including two 200 MW plants).": 0,
    "Armenia will support construction of solar PV power plants up to 500 kW without licensing and allow sale of excess electricity to the grid through net metering, enabled by 2016 amendments to the energy laws.": 0,
    "Armenia targets total installed capacity of autonomous producers to reach 100 MW by 2023 (as envisaged by the Energy Sector Development Strategy up to 2040).": 0,
    "The RA Government adopted a decree on applying measures for energy saving and increasing energy efficiency in facilities built at the expense of state funds, and subsequent legal/technical regulations requiring energy efficiency compliance in new residential buildings and in state-funded construction/renovation projects.": 0,
    "Armenia aims to reduce electricity distribution losses to 6.4% in 2027 under Electric Networks of Armenia's 2016-2027 investment program.": 0,
    "Armenia plans to reach total small hydropower plant (SHPP) capacity of 430 MW by 2023, supported by the Hydro Energy Development Concept and 15-year Power Purchase Agreements under the Energy Law.": 0,
    "Under the Strategy and Action Plan, Armenia will construct medium utility-scale solar PV power plants totaling 175 MW by end-2024, including Masrik-1 (55 MW) in 2022 and additional 120 MW by end-2024.": 0,
    "Under the Strategy and Action Plan, Armenia envisages construction of two 200 MW solar PV plants (400 MW total) in 2023 and 2024, including the 200 MW 'Ayg-1' plant.": 0,
    "Armenia will support installation of solar PV plants up to 5 MW through tariff policy and power purchase agreements, targeting 315 MW of such PV capacity by 2030.": 0,
    "Armenia established a basic national MRV system with inter-agency coordination and verification under the Ministry of Environment, and indicates that legal/formal arrangements are still needed to specify institutional obligations for climate data provision and quality assurance.": 0,
    "The Government of Armenia approved RA Government Protocol Decision N 49-8 (8 December 2016) approving a list of measures (including for 2017–2021) to fulfill obligations under international environmental conventions including the UNFCCC and Paris Agreement, and assigning responsible agencies.": 1,
    "Under Protocol Decision N 49-8 (2016), Armenia assigned the Ministry of Environment responsibility for overall coordination of GHG inventories, national communications, biennial update reports, and establishment of the MRV system.": 1,
    "Armenia established an Inter-agency Coordinating Council on UNFCCC implementation by Prime Minister Decree N 955 (2012), approving its composition and rules of procedure.": 1,
    "Armenia developed and submitted a proposal to reform the Inter-agency Coordinating Council on Climate Change to strengthen coordination and civil society participation, including raising chairmanship to Vice PM and creating four permanent working groups plus a temporary working group; approval is being pursued (consultations toward PM approval in 2021).": 1,
    "Armenia developed a draft Law 'On Atmospheric Air Protection' to set up a unified system for recording hazardous substances and GHG emissions; it is being finalized and intended for government approval/submission in 2021.": 1,
    "Armenia approved the CEPA Implementation Roadmap (PM Decision 666-L) requiring establishment of a national greenhouse gas inventory system and a national MRV mechanism by 2026.": 1,
    "Armenia amended the Law on Ozone Depleting Substances on 26 May 2020 to include HFCs, renaming it the Law on Protection of the Ozone Layer, and adopted Government Decision No 1368-N (20 August 2020) approving a list of 18 HFC gases.": 1,
    "Climate Change-related Statistics was developed and adopted in February 2020 by a Resolution of the State Council on Statistics, setting priorities/actions to improve the climate change-related national statistical system including data for GHG inventories and mitigation/adaptation efforts.": 1,
    "Armenia proposed a continuous GHG inventory data-collection approach based on MoUs: an MoU between the Ministry of Environment and the Statistics Committee for current-scope data provision, plus MoUs with other state organizations, utility companies/natural monopolies, and (if needed) private sector data via the Statistics Committee.": 1,
    "Armenia developed and had approved by the CDM Executive Board an updated standardized ex-ante grid emission factor baseline for the next three years (approved February 2021) to support unified assessment of mitigation effects for renewable energy and energy efficiency activities.": 1,
    "Armenia is establishing a building-sector MRV system through the UNDP-GCF project 'De-risking and Scaling-up Investment in Energy Efficient Building Retrofits', including finalizing and submitting to EPIU a roadmap for piloting EMIS in public buildings and monitoring methodology for energy savings and GHG reductions, and supporting EMIS establishment in municipalities/public entities.": 1,
    "Armenia developed a draft Government Decision to approve the National Framework Strategy on Adaptation to Climate Change Impacts for 2021–2030 and the Action Plan for 2021–2025, which envisages establishing an NAP Accountability, Monitoring and Evaluation (AME) process building on the national MRV system.": 1,
    "Armenia initiated the UNDP-GEF CBIT project 'Building Armenia's national transparency framework under Paris Agreement' to establish national institutional arrangements for an enhanced transparency framework and shift from ad hoc reporting to continuous MRV to track progress against NDC commitments and meet reporting requirements.": 1
  }
